7 July 2010The Inter-Ministerial Committee tasked to deal with xenophobic threats and violence will brief members of the media following a meeting to discuss an integrated programme of action by government and civil society to avert or deal with xenophobic threats and violence.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: Thursday, 8 July 2010 Time: 12h00 Venue: Media Room, Department of International Relations and Cooperation 460 Soutpansberg Road, Rietondale, PretoriaThe IMC is convened by the Minister of Police and includes the Ministers of Home Affairs, Social Development, State Security, Basic Education, Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Arts and Culture as well as International Relations and Cooperation.For media enquiries contact Zweli Mnisi Cell: 082 045 4024Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)